Great Thai food for a great price My favorites here are the pad ki mao, tomyum soup, and their curries. The pad ki mao is a slightly spicy noodle dish with basil and bean sprouts. I love it Tom yum soup is nice and hot with just the amount of spice and lemongrass. Comes with seafood and goes very well with sticky rice. I’m a big fan of the Penang red curry with pork and with sticky rice, one portion is enough to feed at least 2 people. The curry is rich without being overpowering and the red curry isn’t as spicy as the green curry. Albeit their green curry is great as well. Have I mentioned I like their sticky rice?  Thai coffee or Thai tea go well with any of those dishes and will receive a high recommendation from me as well.

My nickname for Bangkok Chef is "Thai Garage," because the door looks like a garage door! I have been coming here for nearly 5 years, and it never fails to delight! My favorite is the #14, sweet and sour...but they will custom make dishes if you order the #16. The spring rolls are amazing, and the dipping sauce is so flavorful your taste buds might jump right off your tongue! THE staff is friendly, the order size is large, the inside seating is very clean but sparse. In 5 years I have never had a bad meal. Ever. That really says something for the quality and consistency of their food.

High quality and super affordable Thai food. This is the original location of Bangkok chef (now open at 4 locations on Oahu) and to me, still the best flavors. Service is fast and friendly. There are a few parking stalls up front and a small parking lot in the back. The  restaurant is open air, so it can get warm at times. We always get the Thai crispy noodles, green curry, cashew chicken, and pad Thai...never been disappointed.

It used to a true hole in the wall, given the tiny space and garage door facade. Now it's gotten much bigger, but it still has that garage door up front. They do good solid Thai fare. The Green Curry is my go to. The Basil Chicken is good too. Everything else I've tried has made me happy. Though I could eat a whole Green Curry in one go, it's big enough that I usually split in half and save it for the next day. You can also get most things a la carte, then add rice on the side. That can probably feed 3 normal people. Parking is tricky, so I go early.

This restaurant was my first experience with Thai food. Upon entering the building the kitchen is visible. I watched as two elderly women (grandmothers) hand mixed a giant bowl of fresh chopped veggies with their bare hands and I thought "maaaan, that's gonna be good!" I ordered the much raved "Pad Thai", and also a side of vegetable egg rolls which were served with a side of whole leaf lettuce leaves, and fresh mint with a tangy dressing. The combination of the salad, and Pad Thai was amazing. Wonderful flavors. All the food was so fresh and prepared well. I would recommend Bangkok Chef to everyone <3
